	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yes. Pretty much by definition, if zero page is being accessed, the high 8 lines of the address bus will all be low. This is the case on the 2A03 and on the standard 6502. (I'm not sure if the external address bus is affected at all when accessing the I/O in zero page of special derivatives like the 6510).

		

		</td>
